From: Bill Atkinson <bill.atkinson@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 22 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Enable P25 ARC4/ADP decryption

Four coordinated changes enable end-to-end ARC4 (ADP, algid 0xaa) decryption:

1. trunk-recorder/recorders/p25_recorder_decode.cc
   flip do_nocrypt 1→0 so the frame assembler attempts decryption

2. trunk-recorder/call_concluder/call_concluder.cc
   remove the early return + file delete for encrypted calls so that
   successfully decrypted calls fall through to normal audio processing

3. Key registration plumbing (four files):
   - trunk-recorder/systems/system_impl.h: add crypt_key_t struct +
     crypt_keys vector + add_crypt_key() inline on System_impl
   - trunk-recorder/config.cc: parse "keys":[{"keyid":N,"algid":N,
     "key":"hexstring"},...] in the per-system JSON block and call
     system->add_crypt_key()
   - trunk-recorder/recorders/p25_recorder_impl.cc: at call start,
     cast System* to System_impl, iterate crypt_keys, push each key
     into both decode blocks via crypt_key()
   - trunk-recorder/recorders/p25_recorder_decode.h/.cc: add
     crypt_key() shim that delegates to op25_frame_assembler->crypt_key()
   - lib/op25_repeater/lib/p25_frame_assembler_impl.h/.cc: override the
     empty virtual crypt_key() and crypt_reset() to forward into p1fdma
     and p2tdma

4. lib/op25_repeater/lib/p25p1_fdma.cc
   In the encrypted voice path, add an "else if (audio_valid)" branch
   that routes decrypted IMBE codewords through the software vocoder
   instead of pushing silence frames. The original silence path is
   kept for the case where no matching key was found (audio_valid=false).

Config example:
  "systems": [{
    "shortName": "MESA",
    ...
    "keys": [
      {"keyid": 1, "algid": 170, "key": "AABBCCDDEE"}
    ]
  }]
  (algid 170 == 0xaa == ADP RC4)

